  "identifier" : {
    "interfaceLanguage" : "swift",
    "url" : "doc:\/\/diagnostics\/documentation\/diagnostics\/mutable-global-variable"
  },
  "kind" : "article",
  "metadata" : {
    "role" : "article",
    "roleHeading" : "Article",
    "title" : "Unsafe mutable global and static variables (MutableGlobalVariable)"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Mutable global and static variables that can be accessed from anywhere can cause data races in your program. Resolve this error by making the state immutable or protecting it with a global actor.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Concurrency checking prohibits mutable global and static variables that are ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "nonisolated",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " because they can be accessed from arbitrary concurrency domains at once and lead to data races.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For example:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "struct Constants {",
            "  static var value = 10",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Building this code with complete concurrency checking will point out the unsafe static variable:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "| struct Constants {",
            "|   static var value = 10",
            "|              |- error: static property 'value' is not concurrency-safe because it is nonisolated global shared mutable state",
            "|              |- note: convert 'value' to a 'let' constant to make 'Sendable' shared state immutable",
            "|              |- note: add '@MainActor' to make static property 'value' part of global actor 'MainActor'",
            "|              `- note: disable concurrency-safety checks if accesses are protected by an external synchronization mechanism"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "If the type of the variable conforms to ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Sendable",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and the value is never changed, a common fix is to change the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "var",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " to a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "let",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " to make the state immutable. Immutable state is safe to access concurrently!",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "If you carefully access the global variable in a way that cannot cause data races, such as by wrapping all accesses in an external synchronization mechanism like a lock or a dispatch queue, you can apply ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "nonisolated(unsafe)",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " to opt out of concurrency checking:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "  nonisolated(unsafe) static var value = 10"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Now consider a static variable with a type that does not conform to ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Sendable",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ":",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "class MyModel {",
            "  static let shared = MyModel()",
            "",
            "  \/\/ mutable state",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This code is also diagnosed under complete concurrency checking. Even though the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "shared",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " variable is a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "let",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " constant, the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "MyModel",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " type is not ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Sendable",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", so it could have mutable stored properties. A common fix in this case is to isolate the variable to the main actor:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "class MyModel {",
            "  @MainActor",
            "  static let shared = MyModel()",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Alternatively, isolate the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "MyModel",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " class to the main actor, which will also make the type ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Sendable",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " because the main actor protects access to all mutable state:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "@MainActor",
            "class MyModel {",
            "  static let shared = MyModel()",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
